Symplichain Hackathon Submission

Name: Abbagani Karthikeya  
Role: Software Engineering Intern Applicant  

Overview:
This repository contains my submission for the Symplichain Software Engineering Intern Hackathon.

The challenge focuses on solving real-world engineering problems across:
- Distributed systems (rate limiting & fairness)
- Mobile architecture
- CI/CD pipeline design
- Production debugging

Approach:
I focused on:
- Practical and scalable solutions
- Using the existing tech stack (Django, Redis, Celery, AWS)
- Clear reasoning instead of over-engineering

Project Structure

Part 1: Shared Gateway Problem:
Designed a request pooling and throttling system to:
- Enforce API rate limit of 3 requests/sec
- Ensure fairness across multiple customers
- Handle retries and failures

Key concepts:
- Redis-based queue
- Celery workers with rate limiting
- Round-robin scheduling for fairness

Part 2: Mobile Architecture:
Designed a mobile-first architecture using:
- React Native (cross-platform)
- Django REST APIs
- JWT-based authentication

Focus:
- Low-friction user experience
- Fast interactions for logistics workflows

 Part 3: CI/CD Pipeline:
Implemented GitHub Actions workflow to:
- Automate deployment on staging & production
- Run migrations and static collection
- Deploy to EC2 using SSH

Suggested improvements:
- Docker for containerization
- Terraform for infrastructure automation

Part 4: Debugging Strategy

Defined a structured debugging approach:
- Step-by-step validation from API → S3 → Celery → AI → DB
- Use of CloudWatch, logs, and monitoring tools
- Root cause isolation methodology

